Here‚Äôs how to sort files by size in Linux.
Standard;
ls -lhS
Reverse;
ls -lhSr
Options used;
-l ‚Äì&gt; print long listing
-h ‚Äì&gt; print human readable sizes
-S ‚Äì&gt; sort by file size
-r ‚Äì&gt; reverse order
Output;
[root@kmon01 log]# ls -lhS&lt;br /&gt; total 70M&lt;br /&gt; -rw-r--r-- 1 root root 36M Mar 31 11:28 messages&lt;br /&gt; -rw-r--r-- 1 root root 15M Mar 31 11:25 cron&lt;br /&gt; -rw-rw-r-- 1 root root 15M Mar 31 04:02 maillog&lt;br /&gt; -rw-rw-r-- 1 root utmp 3.

